<h3>What is the best cold email tool in 2026?</h3>
<p>Instantly.ai is the best cold email tool for most users — unlimited email accounts, strong deliverability infrastructure, and a starting price of $37/month. For agencies managing multiple clients, Smartlead is the stronger choice. For hyper-personalized outreach with AI enrichment, Clay paired with Instantly is the most powerful combination.</p>

<h3>How much does cold email software cost?</h3>
<p>Cold email tools range from $36/month (Saleshandy Outreach Starter) to $159/month (Lemlist Outreach Scale) for individual users. Agency plans with unlimited client accounts typically run $94–$197/month. Apollo.io has a free tier with 50 email credits per month. Clay starts at $149/month for AI-enriched personalization workflows.</p>

<h3>What is the difference between cold email tools and sales engagement platforms?</h3>
<p>Cold email tools (Instantly, Smartlead, Lemlist, Saleshandy) focus specifically on email deliverability, inbox rotation, and outbound sequencing. Sales engagement platforms (Outreach, Salesloft, Apollo) add phone, LinkedIn, and CRM integration on top of email. Cold email tools are cheaper and easier to set up; SEPs are more comprehensive but cost 5–10x more and require IT involvement for deployment.</p>

<h3>Is cold email legal?</h3>
<p>Cold email to business contacts is legal in the US under CAN-SPAM (2003), provided you include a physical address, a working unsubscribe mechanism, and accurate sender information. In the EU, GDPR requires a legitimate interest basis for B2B cold email. Canada's CASL is the strictest — it requires express or implied consent. All major cold email tools include built-in unsubscribe handling and compliance features. This is not legal advice; consult a lawyer for your specific situation.</p>

<h3>How do I improve cold email deliverability?</h3>
<p>The four most impactful actions: (1) configure SPF, DKIM, and DMARC on your sending domain, (2) run a warmup tool for 30+ days before your first campaign, (3) use inbox rotation across multiple accounts and domains, and (4) verify your contact list to keep bounce rates below 3%. All major cold email tools provide guides for steps 1–3. NeverBounce and ZeroBounce are the standard tools for step 4.</p>

<h3>Can I use Gmail or Outlook for cold email?</h3>
<p>Technically yes, but Gmail limits you to 500 emails per day (2,000 for Google Workspace) and Outlook limits you to 300 per day. More importantly, sending cold email from your primary business domain risks damaging your domain reputation if campaigns perform poorly. The standard practice is to use separate sending domains (e.g., getcompanyname.com, trycompanyname.com) and connect them to a dedicated cold email tool.</p>

